To be an introverted creative freelancer and place great value on privacy, this should not be a contradiction, but it often is. Most online sources and coaches advise working with the (evil) tech giants and being extroverted. Advertise here, follow the algorithm, show your personality. Get a blue badge for that service, be available around the clock, answer inquiries with a video of yourself, respond immediately. Video, video, video.
1/3
For me, it is a year of changes.
I do not want to feed the tech giants with money, data, and my energy. Or coaches who have their own extroverted solution and try to sell it to everyone. I am looking for new ways to run my business and am simultaneously fighting against my long-held belief that one must do things a certain way to succeed.
Wish me luck!
The first steps I have already taken.
I have terminated my Facebook account, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deleted my private WhatsApp account.
I also removed Google Analytics, the last external tracker, from my website yesterday and feel good about it.
Recently, I subscribed to a European CRM to have better DSGVO support, and will move my business in this direction in the coming weeks.
I have transferred my MX account to Proton and now have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC, without having to pay Google for normal email validation.
3/3
